@node "bri" "News in Brief"

@{fg shine} News in Brief@{fg text}

 @{b}Epic sign AF1@{ub}
           Epic Marketing have signed Alien Formula One. The amazing game with
 amazing speed an graphics has made a big impression after being featured on all
 the Amiga magzines in the UK. Alien Formula One was reviewed last issue and
 earned itself 91% overall. Hopefully we will be able to get a quick interview
 with epic for next issue!

 @{b}A1200's back!@{ub}
           Wizard Developments are re-stocking the last stocks of the Amiga 1200
 so if you want another A1200 or want to upgrade then get in touch with Wizard
 on 01322 527800 as they are limited stock.

 @{b}A600 goes o3o@{ub}
           At last the Amiga 600 gets power. Until now Amiga 600 owners could only
 match the speed of a basic A1200 owner but thats all changed as you can now get
 a spanking new 030 accelerator. 25MHz 4MB - £99.95 / 25MHz 8MB - £115.95 /
 42MHz 4MB - £115.95 / 42MHz 8MB - £129.95. @{B}Avalible from :@{ub} Power Computing
 01234 851500

 @{b}CD-Rom hits big time@{ub}
           Up until now games on CD have been a thing of the future for Amiga owners
 but now it seems that games on disk are suddenly a thing of the past. Most games
 now will at least require a CD-Rom maybe even soon an accelerator, GFX card and sound
 card. Who knows what will happen but it looks like time to splash out on a CD-Rom.

 @{b}Imagine stays@{ub}
           Imagine is going to stick with the Amiga. Impulse were threatening to pull
 out of the Amiga market as there was not a big response to recent versions of Imagine
 This however all changed when they released version 5 for just $100. They say they
 will definalty be producing Imagine 6.

 @{b}CALLING Norwich Amiga users@{ub}
           The Norwich Amiga Users Group are looking for new members, they hold
 their meetings every fortnight at the Belvedere Community Centre off Dereham road
 in Norwich. They welcome any Amiga user no matter what experience they have with
 an Amiga. For more information phone 01603 867663.

 @{b}Power Amiga@{ub}
           Direct Software's Power Amiga has finnally been released, it was released
 at the World Of Amiga show in London, England. In case you didn't know it inclueds
 CD-Rom, 1 gig HD, 22 meg, Monitor, Zorro Slots, 3D chip, 64 Bit, 060. The full
 set-up will cost you £1.499 and it looks to be a good deal.

