@node "Evil" "Evil's Doom"

@{fg shine} Evil's Doom@{fg text}

           For those of you that have been waiting for a new Dungeon Master game
 your wait is finally over. It's been a long time waiting but I think the wait was
 worth it. As soon as you load the game and see the title screen you know the game
 is going to be a blinder. The graphics are superb and the music is so good it makes
 you feel like your actually there. At the start you have to go to different locations
 on the map and talk to different people, some of the people you talk to will join
 your party others just won't want to talk to you. You start off with two charictors
 and it's up to you who becomes the other two. Every location has a different piece
 of music which makes the game huge. The demo I have tried was 2.2meg LHA'ed. You
 may think spending all that money downloading this demo isn't worth it but let
 me tell you now you've probably never seen a game as good as it. Once you've
 selected your party you progress into the dungeons, the dungeons are as good as the
 rest of the game, basiclly you have to go round different floors opening doors,
 solving puzzles and killing baddies. Overall this games is @{b}GREAT@{ub} there is
 only one problem, the full game has to be bought all the way from Croatia. Don't
 worry thought i've heard rumours that Direct Software UK might be publishing it
 and theres always some truth in rumours.

